1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:02,500
Start on the exact operational screen for this guide.

2
00:00:02,500 --> 00:00:05,000
Payments identifies money risk; Booking Detail authorizes action.

3
00:00:05,000 --> 00:00:07,500
Start with the risk tiles: collection, held deposits, settlement, and long-term exposure.

4
00:00:07,500 --> 00:00:10,000
For unpaid approved bookings, confirm the customer, booking, amount, and reason.

5
00:00:10,000 --> 00:00:12,500
Customer-facing money actions need booking context and an audit trail.

6
00:00:12,500 --> 00:00:15,000
Check the action history after reminders, copied links, refunds, releases, or settlements.

7
00:00:15,000 --> 00:00:17,500
Do not charge, refund, release, or apply a deposit until amount, reason, and booking status all match.

8
00:00:17,500 --> 00:00:20,000
Open the booking before any charge, refund, or deposit action.

9
00:00:20,000 --> 00:00:22,500
Copying a payment link records a money action in the audit trail.
